To give extensions more control over the terminal panel I'm proposing the following:

``` ts
export namespace window {
  export const onDidOpenTerminal: Event<Terminal>;
  export let terminals: Terminal[];
}
```

A solid use case for this is to represent the terminals as tabs somewhere in the UI https://github.com/Tyriar/vscode-terminal-tabs

- VSCode Version: 1.5.3
- OS Version: Ubuntu 16.0.4

I have configured my own tasks.json. It starts a webpack build and works fine at matching problems raised by tslint and stylelint (warnings are well collected in the problem panel and in the status bar), here is the config :

``` javascript
{
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "command": "npm",
  "isShellCommand": true,
  "args": [ "run" ],
  "tasks": [
    {
      "taskName": "build:dev",
      "isBuildCommand": true,
      "isTestCommand": false,
      "problemMatcher": [
        {
          "owner": "pm_stylelint",
          "severity": "error",
          "pattern": [
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+(\\S+)\\sin\\s(\\S*)$",
              "severity": 1,
              "file": 2
            },
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+stylelint:\\s\\S*(src[^:]*):(\\d+):(\\d+):\\s(.*)$",
              "line": 2,
              "column": 3,
              "message": 4
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "owner": "pm_tslint",
          "severity": "error",
          "pattern": [
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+(\\S+)\\sin\\s(\\S*)$",
              "severity": 1,
              "file": 2
            },
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+\\[(\\d+),\\s(\\d+)\\]:\\s(.*)$",
              "line": 1,
              "column": 2,
              "message": 3
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

I have a watch:dev npm script which is simply the build:dev with a --watch arguments (required by webpack cli). The watch:dev tasks is not able to report any error while the output of build:dev and watch:dev are the same, here is my modified tasks.json for this watch:dev command :

``` javascript
{
  "version": "0.1.0",
  "command": "npm",
  "isShellCommand": true,
  "args": [ "run" ],
  "tasks": [
    {
      // The two lines below are the only differences with the build:dev tasks.json
      "taskName": "watch:dev",
      "isWatching": true,
      "isBuildCommand": true,
      "isTestCommand": false,
      "problemMatcher": [
        {
          "owner": "pm_stylelint",
          "severity": "error",
          "pattern": [
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+(\\S+)\\sin\\s(\\S*)$",
              "severity": 1,
              "file": 2
            },
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+stylelint:\\s\\S*(src[^:]*):(\\d+):(\\d+):\\s(.*)$",
              "line": 2,
              "column": 3,
              "message": 4
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "owner": "pm_tslint",
          "severity": "error",
          "pattern": [
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+(\\S+)\\sin\\s(\\S*)$",
              "severity": 1,
              "file": 2
            },
            {
              "regexp": "^\\s+\\[(\\d+),\\s(\\d+)\\]:\\s(.*)$",
              "line": 1,
              "column": 2,
              "message": 3
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Can someone spot any configuration error in the second file or give me some tricks to debug it ?
